lped to launch Africa Now, Bonham’s contemporary African art sale in 2009, he has worked on other noteworthy gallery and curatorial projects and continues to advise on several collections focused in this area globally. Since founding TAFETA, the gallery has remained a leading purveyor of important 20th-century artists of African descent, whilst constantly showcasing new contemporary talent. The central London gallery continues to place works from established and emerging artists with important private collections, as well as established institutions such as the Smithsonian National Museum of African Arts in Washington, D.C. The gallery has also gone on to be recognized as a leading force in the contemporary African art space, showcasing in the prestigious European Fine Art Fair (TEFAF) in March 2020. Juan Perez <img loading="lazy" class="wp-image-557385 aligncenter lazyload" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i2.wp.com/businessday.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/image7.jpeg?resize=383,383&amp;ssl=1" alt="" width="383" height="383" data-srcset="https://i2.wp.com/businessday.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/image7.jpeg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/businessday.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/image7.jpeg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i2.wp.com/businessday.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/image7.jpeg?resize=100%2C100&amp;ssl=1 100w, https://i2.wp.com/businessday.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/image7.jpeg?resize=512%2C512&amp;ssl=1 512w, https://i2.wp.com/businessday.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/image7.jpeg?w=700&amp;ssl=1 700w" sizes="(max-width: 383px) 100vw, 383px" data-recalc-dims="1"><img loading="lazy" class="wp-image-557385 aligncenter lazyload jetpack-lazy-image" src="https://i2.wp.com/businessday.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/image7.jpeg?resize=383,383&amp;ssl=1" alt width="383" height="383" data-recalc-dims="1" data-lazy-srcset="https://i2.wp.com/businessday.ng/wp-content/